<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="329" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="50.[2005,2601,1246,1673]" lastBlockId="50.[1388,2599,1683,3130]" pageId="50" pageNumber="329">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schrenk" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[2006,2372,1369,1398]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Alexandromys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="50" pageNumber="329" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maximowiczii">Alexandromys maximowiczii</taxonomicName>
is in subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ognev" authorityYear="1914" box="[2006,2184,1408,1437]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Alexandromys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="50" pageNumber="329" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Alexandromys</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schrenk" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[2301,2471,1408,1437]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Alexandromys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="50" pageNumber="329" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maximowiczii">maximowiczii</taxonomicName>
species group. Morphologically and genetically, it 1s sister species to the A. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kovalskaya &amp; Sokolov" authorityYear="1980" box="[2427,2568,1482,1515]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Alexandromys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="50" pageNumber="329" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="evoronensis">evoronensis</taxonomicName>
+ A. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Orlov &amp; Kovalskaya" authorityYear="1978" box="[2050,2193,1526,1555]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Alexandromys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="50" pageNumber="329" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mujanensis">mujanensis</taxonomicName>
clade. Within A. maximowiczi1, there are two distinct mtDNA clades: western (Buryatia and south-western part of Zabaykalsky Krai) and eastern (middle part of Amur River Basin). Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="329" type="synonymic_list">
